  <bioghist id="aspace_10dc1e909bb5a873f02037dd3360f187">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>F. Clifton White did graduate work at Cornell University from 1945-1947 and was later active in Republican political campaigns. He was also a faculty advisor at Ithaca College and Cornell University, a social science instructor at Cornell, and a political science lecturer at Ithaca College. He is president of F. Clifton White &amp; Associates, Inc., a public affairs, political counseling, and government relations firm.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_723a43d1e97237d1632be681b77bded5">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Personal papers of F. Clifton White relating to political campaigns from 1960-1970, mainly Barry Goldwater's 1964 presidential campaign.</p>  </scopecontent>
